es: Nunca estarÃ© de acuerdo con la politica de bukele, pero dos matices en este asunto: aquÃ­ en colombia el nivel de hacinamiento y anarquÃ­a en las cÃ¡rceles es tal que muchos viven un verdadero infierno allÃ¡ adentro, peor que el que ese dictadorzuelo intencionalmente les hace vivir a los presos allÃ¡. Y aun asÃ­, aquÃ­ salen a delinquir. Entonces ni es tan sencillo como solo encerrarlos, ni es que aquÃ­ estÃ©n mejor los que si estÃ¡n encerrados. Pero eso de soltarlos, como propone Petro, ya es irse al otro extremo. Creo que AquÃ­ en america latina, en materia penitenciaria, no hay absolutamente ningÃºn buen referente. Segundo, a los que critican solo a Petro, les recuerdo que ninguno de los gobiernos pasados ha expandido la capacidad carcelaria. Por mas bocones que sean de duro contra el crimen, es una amenaza sin dientes dado el estado actual del sistema de prisiones. Solucionar ese problema deberÃ­a ser de las cosas en las que un mÃ­nimo consenso entre partidos deberia lograrse fÃ¡cilmente, no me explico como llevamos dÃ©cadas en esas.
en: I will never agree with Bukele's politics, but there are two nuances in this matter: here in Colombia the level of overcrowding and anarchy in the prisons is such that many live a true hell in there, worse than the one that this dictator intentionally makes them live the prisoners there. And even so, here they go out to commit crimes. So it's not as simple as just locking them up, nor is it that those who are locked up are better off here. But that of releasing them, as Petro proposes, is already going to the other extreme. I think that here in Latin America, in penitentiary matters, there is absolutely no good reference. Second, to those who only criticize Petro, I remind you that none of the past governments have expanded prison capacity. As loud-mouthed as they are tough on crime, he's a toothless menace given the current state of the prison system. Solving this problem should be one of the things in which a minimum consensus between parties should be easily achieved, I don't understand how we have spent decades on those.
